The course gives overview about the language planning. Also the history of the Estonian language planning is introduced. The course also includes the discussions of the participants and the analyses of the texts from the different periods.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The course addresses language planning in a broad sense, from goverment policies to listener-initiated corrections in everyday conversations: why and how is it done in general, and how in particular has it been done in Estonia in the last 100+ years.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  After completing the course, participants are aware of possible motives behind regulatory activities in language planning and can justify their related preferences. Participants also know the main periods of the history of the Estonian language planning.
